Target Users:-
Working professionals who prefer quick and convenient online booking
College students who want easy access to salon services
Busy individuals who donâ€™t want to book appointments through calls
Users looking for flexible scheduling and rescheduling options
This app is designed for mobile-first users who value speed, clarity, and convenience.

Booking Flow Logic:-
The booking flow is designed step-by-step to reduce confusion and make decisions easy.

Flow Structure:
1- Onboarding (Login / Sign Up / OTP)
    Secure and quick authentication
    OTP verification ensures trust and security
2- Dashboard (Service Category Screen)
    Users see available service categories immediately
    Visual cards improve scannability
    Reduces time to find the desired service
3- Service Detail Page
    Displays service description, duration, price
    Helps users make informed decisions before booking
4- Select Specialist
    Shows a list of available specialists
    Builds trust through profile and ratings (if added)
    Allows personalization
5- Select Date & Time
    Shows available slots only
    Prevents double booking
    Reduces user frustration
6- Booking Summary
    Shows complete details:
    Service
    Specialist
    Date & Time
    Price
    Allows users to review before confirming
    Reduces errors
7- Confirmation Page
    Booking success message
    Provides assurance and clarity
    Builds user confidence
8- Booking History
    Separate tabs for:
    Upcoming bookings
    Past bookings
    Helps users track appointments easily
9- Reschedule Page
    Allows users to modify the date/time
    Improves flexibility
    Reduces cancellation rates
10- Notification Page
    Sends reminders
    Keeps users updated about booking status
    Improves engagement

UX Decisions & Rationale:-

1. Step-by-Step Booking
The booking flow is divided into multiple screens to prevent overwhelming the user.
Reason: Improves clarity and reduces drop-offs.

2. Clear Information Hierarchy
Each screen has one primary action.
Reason: Helps users focus and complete tasks faster.

3. Booking Summary Before Confirmation
Users review all booking details before final confirmation.
Reason: Prevents errors and increases trust.

4. Separate Booking History (Upcoming & Past)
Bookings are categorised for easy tracking.
Reason: Improves accessibility and management.

5. Reschedule Feature
Users can modify appointments instead of cancelling and rebooking.
Reason: Increases flexibility and user satisfaction.

How This Design Improves User Experience:-

Reduces booking time
Minimizes confusion
Provides transparency (price, duration, specialist)
Allows flexible scheduling
Improves trust with confirmation and notifications
Enhances overall usability through structured navigation
